{"TopicId":225019,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Is there any way for steam to track hours on a modded build?","CreatedByName":"Brody.mack","CreatedById":231328,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-03T16:49:12Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Brody.mack","CreatedById":231328,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-03T16:49:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m new to the modding scene and found a couple of guides that told me to make a separate instance of KSP to mod so the folder in Steam is a vanilla backup. That seems to be the smartest way, but I still want to have Steam track the hours I have played KSP. Is there a way to allow Steam to track the mod hours while also keeping a backup?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Poppa Wheelie","CreatedById":218525,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-04T16:35:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E will track your hours separately for each of your KSP instances.\u00A0\u00A0Is this what you are after?\u00A0 So you can keep your own total time played stats?\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think there\u0027s any method of \u0022registering\u0022 your various instance locations with Steam.\u00A0 Steam is aware of only one instance.\u00A0 So I don\u0027t see a way for Steam to provide you this capability.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-04T16:43:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSteam will track play time for you if you use this option to add your extra instance and then launch it from within Steam:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022wIzh1pF.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002245.06\u0022 height=\u0022219\u0022 width=\u0022486\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/wIzh1pF.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Brody.mack","CreatedById":231328,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-04T20:50:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224395654\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022225019\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221717518929\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022218525\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Poppa Wheelie\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Poppa Wheelie said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E will track your hours separately for each of your KSP instances.\u00A0\u00A0Is this what you are after?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, that sounds about right. I was not aware that \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E did that!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224395655\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022225019\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221717519411\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156657\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HebaruSan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, HebaruSan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSteam will track play time for you if you use this option to add your extra instance and then launch it from within Steam:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/wIzh1pF.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022wIzh1pF.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002245.06\u0022 height=\u0022219\u0022 width=\u0022486\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/wIzh1pF.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll try this too!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, this was helpful!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}